parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the transmission makes unusual noises
the overdrive light flashes
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into gear
the vehicle lunges or surges forward
the RPMs increase or decrease erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to stall or become difficult to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the 4-wheel drive system can cause the vehicle to lose traction, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle unexpectedly shifts into 4-wheel drive
the vehicle has difficulty shifting into 4-wheel drive
the 4-wheel drive indicator light flashes or remains on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lift Gate Glass Window Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the rear lift gate glass window can cause injuries, damage to the vehicle, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The rear lift gate glass window shatters suddenly
often without warning
and can cause injuries
especially if occupants are nearby. The glass may shatter due to a faulty hinge
ball stud bracket
or other structural issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Lift Gate Hinge and Ball Stud Bracket Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear lift gate hinge and ball stud bracket can cause the glass window to fall, leading to injuries, damage to the vehicle, and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The rear lift gate hinge and ball stud bracket may fracture
disengage
or break
causing the glass window to fall or become misaligned. This can occur suddenly
without warning
and may be accompanied by a rattling or creaking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Panel and Body Mount Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear panel and body mounts can cause structural damage to the vehicle, leading to safety concerns and potentially accidents.
symptoms: The rear panel may crack or shatter
and the body mounts may deteriorate
causing the vehicle's structure to weaken. This can lead to a loss of support for the rear lift gate and glass window
increasing the risk of accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and gear shifter can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or become difficult to control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission may leak fluid
and the gear shifter may break off or become stuck
making it difficult to shift gears or control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system and interior lighting can cause safety concerns, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: The interior lighting may remain illuminated
leak water
or cause electrical issues
leading to safety concerns and potentially accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Wheel bearing failure can cause the wheel to detach from the vehicle, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Abnormal noise
vibration
or clunking sound from the wheel area
wheel detachment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Broken rear coil springs can cause the vehicle to sag, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Sagging rear suspension
broken or cracked coil springs
noise or vibration from the rear suspension.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Body mount failure can cause the vehicle body to separate from the frame, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Noise or vibration from the body or frame
sagging or uneven body alignment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power or stall, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
loss of power or stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Air bag wiring harness failure can cause the air bag to malfunction or fail to deploy in an accident, leading to potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Air bag warning light illumination
faulty air bag deployment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cruise control failure can cause the vehicle to accelerate or decelerate unexpectedly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: Cruise control malfunction
unexpected acceleration or deceleration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rear stabilizer link failure can cause the vehicle to lose stability and control, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: Noise or vibration from the rear suspension
loss of stability or control.
